entry.title: A Barbecue Craze in China Shows Why Its Economy Is Undercooked
entry.content: The trajectory of the city of Zibo—from industrial backwater to meat-grilling vacation hot spot—reflects the bitter reality of China’s postpandemic recovery.

entry.title: Wagner Begins Handoff of Ukraine's Bakhmut to Russia's Military
entry.content: The head of the Russian paramilitary group, Yevgeny Prigozhin, said his fighters are handing over the city to Russian regular troops following a monthslong battle.

entry.title: Pakistan's Opposition Begins to Crack After Thousands Arrested
entry.content: Supporters of former Prime Minister Imran Khan say the government is trying to hobble a political threat ahead of elections.
